  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (text "DISPLAY & UI DESIGN NOTES:\n\n1) ST7789 TFT (LCD1):\n   SPI mode: CLK=IO15, MOSI=IO25 (VSPI bus)\n   CS=IO26, DC=IO12, RST=IO14, BL=IO13 (PWM LEDC)\n   Series 22Ω on SPI lines: reduces ringing, improves EMC\n   Pull-up 10k on RST: ensures clean reset at power-on\n   Backlight: PWM via IO13, LEDC channel 0\n   IO12 is strapping pin - must not be driven HIGH at boot\n   (DC pin is idle LOW during boot since MCU GPIO defaults input)\n\n2) EC11 Rotary Encoder (ENC1):\n   A = IO2, B = IO4 (interrupt-capable pins)\n   SW = IO5 (push button, GPIO interrupt)\n   All pull-up to 3V3_MAIN with 10kΩ\n   Debounce: 10nF on A and B channels only\n   (Software debounce handles SW button)\n   Compatible with original ATS-Mini firmware encoder handling\n\n3) Power Switch (SW3):\n   SPDT slide switch: OFF position disconnects VBAT from LDO inputs\n   Required since ESP32-WROVER-E has no deep-sleep power path\n   Install on case side panel\n\n4) PCB placement:\n   TFT connector near board edge for flex cable routing\n   Encoder at top-right corner of board\n   Power switch at left side\n   Status LED visible through case cutout\n\n5) IO12 WARNING:\n   IO12 is a strapping pin (MTDI). It must be LOW or floating at boot.\n   ST7789 DC pin is connected here. GPIO defaults to input on reset,\n   and the TFT does not drive the line, so this is safe.\n   Verify by checking voltage on IO12 at power-on before TFT init."
    (at 20 200)
    (effects (font (size 1.7 1.7)) (justify left))
  )
)
